---
interface Props {
	title: string;
}

const { title } = Astro.props;
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="description" content="Latest Government Job Updates" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>{title}</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<nav>
			<div class="nav-content">
				<div class="logo">GovtJobUpdates</div>
				<div class="nav-links">
					<a href="/" class="active">Home</a>
					<a href="/about">About</a>
					<a href="/contact">Contact</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</nav>
		<slot />
		<footer>
			<p>Â© 2024 GovtJobUpdates. All rights reserved.</p>
		</footer>
	</body>
</html>
<style is:global>
	:root {
		--accent: 136, 58, 234;
		--accent-light: 224, 204, 250;
		--accent-dark: 49, 10, 101;
		--accent-gradient: linear-gradient(
			45deg,
			rgb(var(--accent)),
			rgb(var(--accent-light)) 30%,
			white 60%
		);
	}
	html {
		font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
		background: #13151a;
		scroll-behavior: smooth;
	}
	body {
		margin: 0;
		min-height: 100vh;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
	}
	nav {
		background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.95);
		padding: 1rem 0;
		position: sticky;
		top: 0;
		z-index: 100;
	}
	.nav-content {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1rem;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
	}
	.logo {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: bold;
		color: white;
	}
	.nav-links {
		display: flex;
		gap: 2rem;
	}
	.nav-links a {
		color: white;
		text-decoration: none;
		padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
		border-radius: 4px;
		transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
	}
	.nav-links a:hover, .nav-links a.active {
		background: rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.2);
	}
	footer {
		margin-top: auto;
		padding: 2rem;
		text-align: center;
		color: white;
		background: rgba(var(--accent-dark), 0.95);
	}
</style>
</boltArtifact>

I've created a modern, responsive website for government job updates with the following features:

1. Clean and professional design with a dark theme
2. Navigation bar with links to different sections
3. Job filtering options (Central/State)
4. Job cards displaying important information:
   - Job title
   - Department
   - Last date to apply
   - Number of vacancies
   - Required qualification
   - Salary range
5. Hover effects and animations for better user experience

To start the development server and see the website:

